<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9816] ALTER TABLE ADD validation is overly strict for re-added collection columns</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9816</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;AlterTableStatement&lt;/tt&gt; ensures that we cannot re-add a collection column of a type that is incompatible with a previously existing, dropped one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It doesn&apos;t make an exception, however, for &lt;tt&gt;frozen&lt;/tt&gt; collections, yet those should be allowed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Code in question:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (dropped != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; (dropped.type == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; || (dropped.type &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; CollectionType &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !type.isCompatibleWith(dropped.type))))
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; InvalidRequestException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;.format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Cannot add a collection with the name %s &quot;&lt;/span&gt; +
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;because a collection with the same name and a different type%s has already been used in the past&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
                columnName, dropped.type == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; ? &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot; : &quot;&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; + dropped.type.asCQL3Type() + &quot;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
